RACE.FOOTNOTES: MISSCZECH set a pressured pace to the turn, drew off for a clear lead and held safely while kept to task. LARIMAR vied two wide to the turn, fell back, continued in a steady effort and gained late to narrow the gap. DANCE LADY broke slowly, trailed the field, closed well inside and got up for show. WE ALL AGREE came in after the start, was taken outside, swung wide leaving the turn and lacked a rally. HOLY TUTTA BELLA was crowded along the rail after the start, stalked the pace along the inside and lacked a stretch response. Following a rider's objection, WE ALL AGREE was disqualified and placed fifth for causing interference after the start. Hand timed.
